traint during this moment of chaos for his opponent=E2=80=94delaying interv=
iews with friendly outlets and only popping on to Fox News sporadically. As=
 James Blair, the Trump campaign=E2=80=99s political director, told
me, =E2=80=9CHe=E2=80=99s been stepping back and letting them set themselve=
s on fire. Don=E2=80=99t interrupt your opponent when they=E2=80=99re light=
ing themselves on fire.=E2=80=9D

Trump may also be distracted by a hard choice of his own: whom to pick as h=
is vice president. With just days remaining until the Republican National C=
onvention begins on Monday, Trump is leveraging the suspense for attention =
and driving advisors =E2=80=9Cnuts,=E2=80=9D according to sources. I=E2=80=
=99m told he=E2=80=99s narrowed it down to Doug Burgum and J.D. Vance, alth=
ough aides freely admit there=E2=80=99s always the very real possibility th=
at he could change his mind. There=E2=80=99s also a pervading sense among s=
ome aides that they should wait as long as possible, to confirm who he is r=
unning against. =E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s like trying to read smoke signals; he=
=E2=80=99s very mercurial. He changed his mind three times in 2016 before s=
ettling on Pence,=E2=80=9D said a longtime advisor. =E2=80=9CHe=E2=80=99s g=
oing to do it at the convention as late as possible.
He=E2=80=99s the master of the tease. He=E2=80=99s going to milk it.=E2=80=
=9D

Trump was expected to announce his running mate sometime before Monday=E2=
=80=99s roll call, so that he could be nominated at the convention with the=
 full ticket, and even leverage the enthusiasm at a rally this Saturday in =
Western Pennsylvania. But the R.N.C. just changed a rule that will now allo=
w him to wait until the last minute on Thursday, just before he accepts the=
 nomination.

The truth, I=E2=80=99m told by multiple sources, is that Trump doesn=E2=80=
=99t really care for Burgam or Vance, and he doesn=E2=80=99t see a running =
mate as a net benefit to his campaign. The idea of a vice presidential cand=
idate receiving even a drop of credit for a Trump win in November irks him.=
 =E2=80=9CHe doesn=E2=80=99t give much of a fuck about it. He doesn=E2=80=
=99t love any of these people; he doesn=E2=80=99t know these people,=E2=80=
=9D said the same gloating Mar-a-Lago denizen. =E2=80=9CWith Burgum, he lik=
es his look, but they haven=E2=80=99t actually spent a
lot of time together, one-on-one, just maybe five, eight times. He doesn=E2=
=80=99t spend time with J.D. He didn=E2=80=99t give a fuck about Mike Pence=
=2E=E2=80=9D Trump does have a strong re=
lationship with Marco Rubio, who=E2=
=80=99s kept himself in the running thanks to the advocacy of Kellyanne Con=
way and Susie Wiles. If not veep, I=E2=80=99m hearing he could be on the sh=
ortlist for secretary of state.

Another source with knowledge of Trump=E2=80=99s veep deliberations said it=
=E2=80=99s come down to a battle between Melania, who prefers Burgum becaus=
e she worked ( https://puck.news/will-doug-burgum-be-trumps-vice-president/=
?utm_campaign=3DThe+Best+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%287%2F11%2F24%29&=
utm_content=3DThe+Best+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%286%2F30%2F24%29&ut=
m_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd=
12a ) with his wife, Kathryn, on an initiative in the White House, and Don =
Jr., who=E2=80=99s been aggressively lobbying for Vance. =E2=80=9CIf it=E2=
=80=99s Melania over
Don Jr., she wins,=E2=80=9D said another source, albeit noting that it was =
the former first lady who encouraged Trump to endorse Dr. Oz over David McC=
ormick in his losing Pennsylvania Senate race. =E2=80=9CThat was a major fu=
ck-up on her part,=E2=80=9D said a former Trump aide. =E2=80=9CIt cost her.=
=E2=80=9D

The aides arguing for Vance are telling Trump that the junior senator=E2=80=
=99s youth would be an asset as a contrast to Biden, and that the Hillbilly=
 Elegy narrative could play well in the Rust Belt, where there seems to be =
a real shot at cracking the Blue Wall in Pennsylvania, Wisconsin, and Michi=
gan. Vance=E2=80=99s moderate-ish position on abortion=E2=80=94he recently =
said abortion pills should remain publicly accessible in states where it=E2=
=80=99s legal=E2=80=94is also seen as an asset. Burgum=E2=80=99s stance as =
governor of North Dakota, where he signed one of the most restrictive abort=
ion bans in the nation, defies Trump=E2=80=99s political instincts about tr=
ying to neutralize the issue. As anyone close
to Trump knows, he believes the G.O.P.=E2=80=99s surprising 2022 midterm lo=
sses had nothing to do with him or his endorsed roster of far-right candida=
tes, and everything to do with abortion.

